<p style="text-align:start"><strong>Hancock Park Rehabilitation &amp; Nursing Center &bull;</strong> in Quincy is a 142-bed skilled center offering short-term and long-term care. Hancock Park has a dedicated Subacute Unit, specializing in cases that are medically complex or rehabilitation-intensive. The center takes pride in providing care that is truly state-of-the art and compassionate.&nbsp;</p>  <p style="text-align:start">Conveniently located near the heart of downtown Quincy, Hancock Park has served as the city&rsquo;s premier nursing center since 1996. The center offers restaurant-style dining, a gift shop, entertainment and recreational activities, a beautifully maintained outdoor courtyard and free parking.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>  <p style="text-align:start">Each resident has access to cable TV and private telephone service. Residents enjoy meals in our elegant dining rooms or in their own room, depending upon individual preference. Some residents elect to have breakfast in one of our intimate dining areas closer to their room.<br /> <br /> Hancock Park is accredited by&nbsp;<a href="http://www.jointcommission.org/" style="outline: none; color: rgb(17, 113, 169); text-decoration: none;" target="_blank">The Joint Commission</a>&nbsp;and is Medicaid/Medicare Certified. The staff is committed to providing high quality medical, nursing and rehabilitative care to allow every resident to experience the best quality of life while maintaining or regaining function, health and well-being.</p>  <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 40px;"> 	<li>Click here to learn more about Skilled Nursing</li> 	<li>Click here for our Rehabilitation Brochure</li> </ul> 